\begin{abstract}\
A gauge $U(1)$ framework was established in 2002 to extend the supersymmetric 
standard model.  It has many possible realizations.  Whereas all have the 
necessary and sufficient ingredients to explain the possible 750 GeV 
diphoton excess, observed recently by the ATLAS Collaboration at the 
Large Hadron Collider (LHC), they differ in other essential aspects. 
A compendium of such models is discussed.
\end{abstract}

