It may also decay into $S_1 S_2$ final states directly and increase its 
total width.  These are then the essential ingredients which could explain 
the 750 GeV observation.

In choosing $n_1$ and $n_4$, if the resulting model has only those 
interactions of Eqs.~(1) and (2), then the $U,D$ particles are 
stable.  They may form bound states with the known quarks and 
become exotic stable matter.  In the following, only cases 
with additional interactions are considered.

